RACE.RACE_TEXT: EVANGELINE DOWNS RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 19000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, For Each $2,500 To $15,000 2 lbs. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FATHER RED was allowed to settle in the early stages then made a five wide bid at the half pole, tipping in to three wide at the quarter pole to take the lead in upper stretch, drifted in in the final sixteenth but was able to hold on for the win. MO CREDO raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then moved up from four wide on the backstretch and launched his bid at the half pole to engage the leader at the quarter pole and fought gamely down the stretch to prove second best. CHICKEN TRUCK was forwardly placed around the first turn then moved up from three wide to stalk the pace, engaged the leaders at the half pole and stuck his head in front briefly and tired in the stretch. K V TARGET raced near the back around the first turn and down the backstretch then made a bid from four wide at the five sixteenths pole to improve position. PEANUT N IKE was off the pace down the backstretch then made a three wide bid a the three furlong pole to move up but flattened out. DARK MATTER pressed the pace from the two path to the three eighths pole and weakened. WESTERN STAR cut the corner going into the first turn to take the lead and set the early pace but was through after a half. LITTLE ROCKY tracked the leaders from off the rail but was never a threat. GOROSTIETA'S LOVE raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then made a mild bid from five wide at the half pole and faltered. INSPECTOR ED broke outward at the start and was out run. AN OBJECTION WAS POSTED, THE JOCKEY OF MO CREDO CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF FATHER RED FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE FINAL SIXTEENTH, AFTER A STEWARDS REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED.
